{
  "stem": "15938.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then he used to go back to the beis medrash.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Everything was around the shul and the beis medrash.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was davening and learning in between and davening again and the learning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was very, very strict.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And as they say, schlepped my brothers with.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And, you know, it was a very cold country.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was very, very. bitter cold, and you had to get up in it very early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was part of life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You didn't question it or criticize it or-- that was how it was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very seriously.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And it was a-- it was a-- in a small town, Shabbos was the event of the week.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and you prepared for it starting on Wednesday and the baking and the cooking and the preparation and-- and because of there were so many people coming from the surrounding towns, we always provided kiddish after shul before they went home because they always had to walk a long time.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all these [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Hatsidish gentlemen used to come and have kiddish in our house and then walk back.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the-- and then we used to go to my older aunt, was older than my-- my father.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, you know, it was stretched out, the Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then we came back and had lunch and sleeping and then learning, learning, learning.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was the-- my father and my brothers, there was-- was always a book open and was learning.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was the main-- that's how I think everybody did it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, as a child, you think whatever you do, the whole world does the same.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But there was nothing much else to do there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
